cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC

This paper deals with energy-efficient power control schemes for small cell base stations (SBS) in wireless networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves modeling and optimization, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the use of content caching and popularity distribution could relate to cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
